desc: Overnight: Showers likely and possibly a thunderstorm. Some of the storms could produce small hail.  Mostly cloudy, with a low around 43. Breezy, with a northeast wind 20 to 26 mph, with gusts as high as 33 mph.  Chance of precipitation is 70%. New rainfall amounts of less than a tenth of an inch, except higher amounts possible in thunderstorms.
Monday: Sunny, with a high near 54. West northwest wind 7 to 13 mph.
Monday Night: Mostly clear, with a low around 40. West northwest wind 6 to 11 mph becoming light and variable  in the evening.
Tuesday: Mostly sunny, with a high near 53. North wind 6 to 8 mph.
Tuesday Night: Partly cloudy, with a low around 39. Northeast wind 3 to 5 mph.
Wednesday: Partly sunny, with a high near 52.
Wednesday Night: Mostly cloudy, with a low around 40.
Thursday: Partly sunny, with a high near 54.
Thursday Night: Mostly cloudy, with a low around 42.
